<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Sollwin on 04-15-2001 09:20 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">  [QUOTE]
Now if you're having fun, by all means swing and whiff. But please don't try to get us to believe that you need the 250 mana for an emergency heal while full mana with C2. You'll be FAR more efficient nuking a bubble and then medding up than standing there full mana whiffing at the mobs.
[/QUOTE]

Two Reason I'm not kidding.

1.  6 Seconds is enough time for a Enchanter to go *Splat*  I can switch from melee and target a chanter in less time then I am locked into the cast of a DD

2.  Yes, I have needed every bit of my mana at a moments notice, that unexpected add can be a real bummer and I find myself chaining to keep a caster living.

I'm sorry Rayne, but I disagree with you.  Why should I blow mana and sit on my butt to med it back?  Even with C2 you only get mana back so fast.  Besides, I've found my DD to be just as unreliable and contributing to the fight as my melee is.

If I'm sitting at FM and NOT doing something else, then I am wasted space.  So I might as well swing, and there's no reason I should not be as effective at it as I can be.

BTW, I do hit pretty consistantly.  So sure, it may not be much damage, but at least I get the satisfaction of knowing I did something and have a bit of fun in the process.  It's safe for the group and keeps us being quite so bored.

I'm not sure when clerics got locked into this mindset of never getting involved in melee.  I can say, from experince, that I can and do do it,  my group members live and we all have a great time.

*As a side note, there are times I do not melee or nuke, mana just does not permit and all my attention focuses on healing and bufing alone.

------------------
Sollwin Lifestar
51st Halfling Vicar of Bristlebane

